The Letter
Most Illustrious Proprietor,

I am currently Tech Lead at Eros Labs(Part incubator, part investment firm backed by Eros Group). I have played different roles during my career, mostly revolving around mobile and web technologies. I have realized that every role was more demanding than the previous one and they required more than more than just being a code geek. Not only that I have been a Code Geek, but at times I would wear different hats labeling Growth Marketer and Product Manager.
  • I am passionate about building products that have an impact on customers' business as well as users' lives and provide solutions to the real-world problems. Understanding the challenges, combined with practical implementations and technologies, has always been my key to designing and delivering products.
  • For almost three years I worked as an IT Consultant and Web Developer with US startups focusing on variety of technologies and different complexity levels of the products.
  • While on papers I am a Tech Lead at Eros Labs, in reality, most of the time I am wearing a mask of a Product Manager who understands tech deeply.
  • I am capable of fulfilling a role for any position that requires analysis of business rules and technical skills, I have specific experience in two main areas that are closely related.
    On the analysis side, I am responsible for taking data from different sources, extracting functional requirements and translating them into detailed requirements.
    On the technical side, as a Tech Lead I am responsible for designing the architecture of the product, writing and reviewing code with utmost quality assurance, deploying and managing self scalable hosting infrastructure, leading the team of developers and UI/UX professionals and ensuring deliverables are completed within the given timeline.
